   - If a path has five unique points and each is connected, it is likely a pentagon (label G), not a kite (label D), unless two pairs of adjacent sides are equal and it obviously fits the kite definition.
   - Do not confuse five-point paths with four-point (kite/rectangle/trapezoid) shapes.
   - If in doubt, confirm shape type by the number of unique vertices and the way edges relate.

